label: Tribal affiliation
definition: Participant considers themselves Adivasi or a tribal person

label: Participant inpatient or outpatient
definition: Participant admitted as an inpatient or seen as an outpatient

label: State moved from in last month
States moved from in last 12 months
Initiated antimalarial treatment
definition: Antimalarial treatment was initiated at the hospital

label: Medication dose
definition: The dose in milligrams a participant took of a given medication. If a participant was on multiple medications and/or took them over multiple timepoints, each drug and time will be counted separately.

label: Antimalarial medication
definition: Antimalarial medication that was given while hospitalized. If a participant was on multiple medications and/or took them over multiple timepoints, each drug and time will be counted separately.

label: Medication timepoint
definition: The timepoint in days that medication was given. Timepoint of 0 indicates when medication was started. If a participant was on multiple medications and/or took them over multiple timepoints, each drug and time will be counted separately.

label: Hemoglobin, at hospital
definition: Hemoglobin measurement done by the hospital. Exact date of measurement unknown

label: Plasmodium species, by FalciVax RDT at hospital
definition: Parasite species identification via an RDT performed by the hospital. Exact date of RDT unknown

label: Plasmodium species, by thick smear microscopy
definition: Parasite species identified in a thick blood smear

label: Plasmodium species, by thin smear microscopy
definition: Parasite species identified in a thin blood smear

label: Plasmodium species, by microscopy at hospital
definition: Parasite species identification via microscopy done by the hospital. Exact date of blood smear unknown

label: Plasmodium falciparum parasitemia (%), by microscopy result
definition: Percent parasitemia per 100 red blood cells in a thin blood smear

label: Plasmodium vivax parasitemia (%), by microscopy result
definition: Percent parasitemia per 100 red blood cells in a thin blood smear

label: Plasmodium malariae parasitemia (%), by microscopy result
definition: Percent parasitemia per 100 red blood cells in a thin blood smear

label: Plasmodium gametocytemia (%), by microscopy result
definition: Percent gametocytemia per 100 red blood cells in a thin blood smear

label: Sample collection date
definition: Date of hospital samples used to determine Plasmodium infection status and hemoglobin levels unknown

label: Sample collection time
definition: Time of hospital samples used to determine Plasmodium infection status and hemoglobin levels unknown
